{"TopicId":157857,"ForumId":25,"TopicTitle":"Airliner Safety Challenge","CreatedByName":"Rath","CreatedById":138223,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-18T10:45:43Z","PageNum":4,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"martiplay28yt","CreatedById":173290,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-27T17:59:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ncan i use AirplanePlus?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"martiplay28yt","CreatedById":173290,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-27T19:52:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnevermind i\u00B4m making\u00A0a stock one\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-27T19:53:40Z\u0022 title=\u002203/27/2017 07:53  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 27, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by martiplay28yt\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NotAnAimbot","CreatedById":151034,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-28T00:38:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222999066\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157857\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490628291\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022162839\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022EpicSpaceTroll139\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, EpicSpaceTroll139 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you tried autostruts and rigid attachment?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThought about it, but I consider them \u0022cheats\u0022 so I didn\u0027t use them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EpicSpaceTroll139","CreatedById":162839,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-28T01:13:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222999879\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157857\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490661504\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022151034\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NotAnAimbot\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n32 minutes ago, NotAnAimbot said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThought about it, but I consider them \u0022cheats\u0022 so I didn\u0027t use them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, if that\u0027s how you view them, you could always use them and then stick an ore tank and/or a few steel plates on to simulate their weight and drag for much fewer parts. Eh, to each his own. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"martiplay28yt","CreatedById":173290,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-28T12:52:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni\u00B4m doing the calculations but i have one problem with the extra points-\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni have 7 engines and need only 2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nso how many points do i get for this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"martiplay28yt","CreatedById":173290,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-28T18:04:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni made a mid size one\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n5-35m/s stall\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n20-the tailstrike rule\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n10-all survive a land in water \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n20-everybody survives a belly-land if done propperly\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n10-has airbrakes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n20- has 7 engines and can run on 2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n851m/s\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3271km\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2 atendants\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n32 pasangers\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nfor the speed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther ipsEmbeddedOther_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=http://imgur.com/86PwYQb\u0022 style=\u0022height:414px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n32 kerbals\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther ipsEmbeddedOther_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=http://imgur.com/PGjeu3x\u0022 style=\u0022height:414px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nfor a clear wiew of the plane\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther ipsEmbeddedOther_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=http://imgur.com/lea6O2i\u0022 style=\u0022height:414px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nintirier wiew\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther ipsEmbeddedOther_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=http://imgur.com/TRTx50k\u0022 style=\u0022height:414px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-28T19:47:21Z\u0022 title=\u002203/28/2017 07:47  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 28, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by martiplay28yt\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Emissing space\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rath","CreatedById":138223,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-29T00:29:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAirplane plus is allowed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NotAnAimbot","CreatedById":151034,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-29T12:23:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E update the scoring board?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"zolotiyeruki","CreatedById":150224,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-30T03:12:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s my entry for the light category. \u00A0I fully admit this sorta exploits the rules by being a fast, super-long-endurance plane. \u00A0I could have probably made it go around kerbin a few more times too (my record is 14!), but this was quick and dirty:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022QYVpGZW.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/QYVpGZW.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nScoring (only including things that both affect the score and that I\u0027ve tested):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMax Speed: 1584m/s\u003Cbr\u003E\nCannot tailstrike on takeoff: 20\u003Cbr\u003E\nSimple air/fuel: 10\u003Cbr\u003E\nNeeds all engines: -20\u003Cbr\u003E\nCan burn up: -10\u003Cbr\u003E\nRange: 10x around Kerbin (plus about 30 min of reserve)\u00A0at approximately 26km altitude, so (626*6.28*10) = 39,313 km\u003Cbr\u003E\nPassengers: 2\u003Cbr\u003E\nDitch in water without damage or losing crew/passengers: 20\u002B10\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nScore:\u003Cbr\u003E\n1584 \u002B 39313/10 \u002B 2*5 \u002B 20 \u002B 10 \u002B 20 \u002B 10 -20-10 = 5555\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E, may I suggest a cap on the number of points available from the aircraft\u0027s range? \u00A0I would suggest a maximum cap of 360 points from that part of the score.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-30T03:27:36Z\u0022 title=\u002203/30/2017 03:27  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 30, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by zolotiyeruki\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MustaKotka","CreatedById":176166,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-30T19:49:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223002449\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157857\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490843572\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150224\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022zolotiyeruki\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 hours ago, zolotiyeruki said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E, may I suggest a cap on the number of points available from the aircraft\u0027s range? \u00A0I would suggest a maximum cap of 360 points from that part of the score.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll just remind you guys that there are other mathematical functions available, too. Roots and logarithms, for example... The coefficients are just a matter of politics but really, those kind of functions would stop mindless spam and make other options more lucrative. Even KSP itself uses nonlinear functions for calculating things like reputation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NotAnAimbot","CreatedById":151034,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-01T13:01:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/138223-rath/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022138223\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/138223-rath/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Rath\u003C/a\u003E, could we get an update on the scoreboard? Already 3 planes have topped points in the superheavy and light categories.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"notsodeadjeb","CreatedById":159342,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-01T20:03:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nK84 Passenger Plane\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSuper heavy ( 80 passengers, two flight attendants, and two pilots)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRange- when flown perfectly( which is NOT all that easy) about 2700\u00A0kilometers\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMax speed- 288 m/s\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo ipsEmbeddedVideo_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/2QsXTX4JV4Q?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#27ae60;\u0022\u003EYour plane cannot tailstrike no matter how hard you pull up on takeoff (20 points)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#27ae60;\u0022\u003EYour plane stalls at less than 50m/s (5 points)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#27ae60;\u0022\u003EYour plane does not need\u00A0\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u00A0to fly stably (20 points)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#27ae60;\u0022\u003EYour plane does not need trim adjustment to fly straight and level. \u00A0This only stacks with the non\u00A0\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u00A0points. (10 points)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#27ae60;\u0022\u003EYour plane has three engines and can fly on two (5 points)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#27ae60;\u0022\u003EYour plane has three engines and can fly on one (30 points)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#27ae60;\u0022\u003EYour plane can belly land with all crew and passengers surviving (20 points)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#27ae60;\u0022\u003EYour plane has airbrakes (10 points)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#27ae60;\u0022\u003EYour plane can ditch in the water with all crew surviving (10 points)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#27ae60;\u0022\u003EYour plane can ditch in the water with no damage (20 points)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#27ae60;\u0022\u003EYour plane can fly on any two engines. - not sure how many points this is, but let\u0027s say 30.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nPoint malus:\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003EYour plane solely relies on alternators on the main engines for power- has one battery, so.. -5 points?\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003E288\u002B(2700/10)\u002B((80*5)*1\u002B(2/2))\u002B175\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003E288\u002B270\u002B400\u002B1\u002B175\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003E=1134!\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003EThats the new lowest score on the super heavy!\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rath","CreatedById":138223,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-02T03:09:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223005605\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157857\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491051705\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022151034\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NotAnAimbot\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, NotAnAimbot said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/138223-rath/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022138223\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/138223-rath/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Rath\u003C/a\u003E, could we get an update on the scoreboard? Already 3 planes have topped points in the superheavy and light categories.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYep, I\u0027m doing it now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: Switched up the engine out points to percentages.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-04-02T04:38:34Z\u0022 title=\u002204/02/2017 04:38  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EApril 2, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Rath\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rath","CreatedById":138223,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-02T03:33:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWAIT IM TOTM?!?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NotAnAimbot","CreatedById":151034,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-02T14:09:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223006491\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157857\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491103999\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022138223\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rath\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, Rath said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWAIT IM TOTM?!?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ncongratz\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EpicSpaceTroll139","CreatedById":162839,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-02T14:54:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222999879\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157857\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490661504\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022151034\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NotAnAimbot\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/27/2017 at 8:38 PM, NotAnAimbot said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(\u002B_\u002B) mobile y u do dis\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyways, I feel like engine out system is hard make work well. On one hand, the new percentage system helps make it applicable to aircraft with any number of engines, and helps to (somewhat) reduce incentive to spam unneeded engines for points.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut on the other hand, it gives the same amount of points to, say, a quadjet aircraft with two engines out as to a twinjet aircraft with one engine out, even though the quadjet is contending with a scenario which is (theoretically) far less likely than that that the twinjet is contending with. To demonstrate the problem, let\u0027s do some math.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor the sake of simplicity, let\u0027s say that there are no uncontained engine failures that take out other engines. We\u0027ll also ignore something like a flock of Canada geese or a volcanic ash cloud that could take out all engines on a plane at once.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSuppose the chance of any given engine going out during a particular flight is 0.01%.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe twinjet has a 2 x 0.01% = 0.02% chance of needing to fly with one of it\u0027s engines out.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMeanwhile, the quadjet has a 4 x 0.01% \u00A0= 0.04% chance of needing to fly with one of it\u0027s engines out. This makes sense, since a quadjet has twice as many engines, thus twice the number of engines that could go bust on any given flight. So at first our system seems reasonable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut we want to know what the chances are of it needing to fly with two engines out. The chances for another engine to go out in a flight once one of them is already out would be 3 x 0.01 = 0.03%. So for two engines to go out that\u0027s 0.04% x 0.03% = 0.000012%! (If you think that math doesn\u0027t work, remember that 100% is probability 1. You divide by 100 before multiplying, then multiply by 100 again later to get the percentage.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo the quadjet is getting the same number of points for coping with a situation that is immensely less likely than that of the twinjet. Hmm...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever awarding points linearly for each engine isn\u0027t great either, as it incentivizes the spamming of engines for large numbers of points... Catch 22 I guess \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-04-02T23:18:44Z\u0022 title=\u002204/02/2017 11:18  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EApril 2, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by EpicSpaceTroll139\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SG Aero","CreatedById":174890,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-02T19:09:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nConsidering the mass amount of explosions I cause, this might not be the best challenge for me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ChaoticPheonix","CreatedById":124657,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-02T21:19:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Og4CZC5.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/Og4CZC5.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;\u0022\u003ESupersonic Passenger Jet - Phoenix Aerospace\u0027s\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#e74c3c;\u0022\u003E\u003Cem\u003EFireStar\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ETested Range: Approx. 2100km\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EMaximum Speed: Mach ~4.5 or 1362m/s\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ECruising Altitude: 18,000m to 20,000m\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EPassenger Capacity: 8\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cfont color=\u0022#2ecc71\u0022\u003ECannot Tailstrike - 20 points\u003C/font\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cfont color=\u0022#2ecc71\u0022\u003EDoes not need \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E to fly stably - 20 points\u003C/font\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#2ecc71;\u0022\u003EDoes not need trim - 10 points\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#2ecc71;\u0022\u003ECan fly on 33.3% of engines - 30 points\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#2ecc71;\u0022\u003EHas airbrakes - 10 points\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cfont color=\u0022#2ecc71\u0022\u003ECan fly on any two engines - assuming 5 points because of 66.6% rule\u003C/font\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cfont color=\u0022#2ecc71\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETotal Bonus: 95 Points\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/font\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EScore\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n1362 \u002B (2100km / 10) \u002B (8 * 5) * 1 \u002B 0 \u002B 95\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n1362 \u002B (210) \u002B (40) \u002B 95\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E1707\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Delay","CreatedById":173586,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-03T16:31:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTried to make a SR-71...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEnded up with a suborbital spaceplane, but it can go into orbit under the right circumstances.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes that still count?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"qzgy","CreatedById":160994,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-03T17:20:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223008044\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157857\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491237088\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173586\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Delay\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n48 minutes ago, Delay said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTried to make a SR-71...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEnded up with a suborbital spaceplane, but it can go into orbit under the right circumstances.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes that still count?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo. Airliner may not leave atmosphere. Its in the rules.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ChaoticPheonix","CreatedById":124657,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-04T00:14:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022vvJSSqX.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/vvJSSqX.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;\u0022\u003ESupersonic Passenger Jet - Phoenix Aerospace\u0027s\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#e74c3c;\u0022\u003ENova\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\nClass: Large\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ETested Range: Approx. 2300km\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EMaximum Speed: Mach ~4.2\u00A0or 1250m/s\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ECruising Altitude: 17,000m\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EPassenger Capacity: 36\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cfont color=\u0022#2ecc71\u0022\u003ECannot Tailstrike - 20 points\u003C/font\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cfont color=\u0022#2ecc71\u0022\u003EDoes not need \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E to fly stably - 20 points\u003C/font\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#2ecc71;\u0022\u003EDoes not need trim - 10 points\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#2ecc71;\u0022\u003ECan fly on 25% of engines - 35\u00A0points\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#2ecc71;\u0022\u003EHas airbrakes - 10 points\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cfont color=\u0022#2ecc71\u0022\u003ECan take off and land immediately - 10 points\u003C/font\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cfont color=\u0022#2ecc71\u0022\u003EHas a way to jettison fuel without speeding up - 10\u003C/font\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cfont color=\u0022#2ecc71\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETotal Bonus: 115 Points\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/font\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EScore\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n1250 \u002B (2300km / 10) \u002B (36\u00A0* 5) * 1 \u002B (2 / 2)\u00A0\u002B 115\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n1250\u00A0\u002B (230) \u002B (180) \u002B 2\u00A0\u002B 115\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E1777\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rath","CreatedById":138223,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-04T01:05:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-----------Rules change-------------\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe no suborbital planes rule is dead, long live the no rocket rule!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Delay","CreatedById":173586,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-04T13:52:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, do I have to activate a parachute by hand or assign it to an action group? Or can I use the staging for that?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ChaoticPheonix","CreatedById":124657,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-04T17:27:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223009056\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157857\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491313931\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173586\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Delay\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Delay said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, do I have to activate a parachute by hand or assign it to an action group? Or can I use the staging for that?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI find it\u0027s easiest to action group it, but any method works fine really.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NotAnAimbot","CreatedById":151034,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-04T22:51:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223009056\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157857\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221491313931\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173586\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Delay\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Delay said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, do I have to activate a parachute by hand or assign it to an action group? Or can I use the staging for that?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI put them as the stage right after the engines and before any ejection modules I\u00A0got on bombers. It can lead to accidental parachute release though, so action grouping might be better.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}